  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased production by members  improved marketing and financial sustainability</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Activities in action plan:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.1 Improved service provision structure to members; action plan available plus financial projections&lt;br&gt;1.2 Continuation of 20 demonstration plots &lt;br&gt;1.3 Provide extension services that are financially sustainable  by ensuring that members who receive extension services market their rice through IDRA&lt;br&gt;2.1 Governance Training&lt;br&gt;2.2 Elaborate new IDRA Strategic Plan incl. marketing plan and financial forecast to become more financially independent.&lt;br&gt;2.3 Enhance financial sustainability of IDRA through internal capitalisation and paid membership services; show added value of IDRA to realize a higher percentage of paid-up members&lt;br&gt;2.4 Improve business plan SINZA Women&#x2019;s Association&lt;br&gt;2.5 Member meeting to explain what services IDRA provides to its members (and what not)&lt;br&gt;2.6 Facilitation of monthly board meetings&lt;br&gt;3.2 3.1 In-house Basic financial management training &#x2013;&lt;br&gt;3.3 Financial management / governance training for SACCOs&lt;br&gt;4.1 Workshop Record keeping and services for members (together with CDRA)&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Increased production by members  improved marketing and financial sustainability for IDRA.&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Partnership between IDRA and Agriterra started in 2010. After shift in Agriterra&#x2019;s approach of having a business advisor based in Zambia  he conducted an organisation assessment to better understand the performance and proposed way forward of the partnership. The organization assessment report is available in which joint activities and objectives have been elaborated.&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
